484
00:25:09.786 --> 00:25:13.816 A:middle
The goal at Pixar is never to
go with just loads and loads

485
00:25:13.816 --> 00:25:16.186 A:middle
of detail and just make
it look like a creature

486
00:25:16.446 --> 00:25:19.246 A:middle
because we've hit this area
called "Uncanny Valley".

487
00:25:19.246 --> 00:25:22.136 A:middle
It's something we try to avoid
very much where you've added

488
00:25:22.136 --> 00:25:25.736 A:middle
so much detail that it
looks too realistic.

489
00:25:26.156 --> 00:25:30.126 A:middle
And at Pixar, we want to find
the essence of these designs.

490
00:25:30.126 --> 00:25:32.366 A:middle
We want to boil it down
to its simplest idea

491
00:25:32.366 --> 00:25:34.576 A:middle
and then really pull
that idea out.

492
00:25:34.806 --> 00:25:36.926 A:middle
And so with all these
photography, I was supposed

493
00:25:36.926 --> 00:25:39.326 A:middle
to take inspiration
but not copy exactly.

494
00:25:39.676 --> 00:25:42.166 A:middle
I was supposed to
find that simple idea.

